<br /><br />
<b><font class="print-title">My Gun Seems to be Smoking....</font></b><br /><br />
<font class="print-sub">Articles / Government<br />
<b>Date:</b> Apr 12, 2004 - 01:59 PM</font>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>
<font class="print-normal">So now that the PDB of August 6 entitled <a href="/modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Sections&amp;file=index&amp;req=viewarticle&amp;artid=1&amp;page=1">Bin Ladin Determined To Strike in US</a> has been declassified, President Bush is declaring that there was not enough detail to act. While the government issued warnings to various agencies in June and July of 2001, there were none posted after August 6th.<br>
<p>In the end this just really raises more questions, especially for the FBI and CIA who allowed known terrorists to roam at will even though there were directives to at least do questioning or further investigations. The FBI cites more than 70 on going investigations. With 56 offices in the US that's a lot of investigating over something that is trivial or non-descript.<br>
<p>Regarding the commission, Richard Ben-Veniste, has noted that there should have been more aggressive steps taken in light of this memo. Until the commission releases their finding though, it remains to be seen if the rest agree.<br /><br />
<br />
</font>
</td></tr>
